The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Saturday, March 06, 2004 				 The essence of spring
																								Springtime has, for long, been associated withbeauty, youth and immortality. And it is this eternal life associated with this season that is being celebrated with aplomb at Idiyas Gallery. The exhibition on display explores the fundamentals of spirituality and captures the effervescence of life through mediums ranging from tempera, watercolours, oils, acrylics and charcoal, and a range of forms including metal, marble and fibreglass. The exhibition showcases the works of Paritosh Sen, Ganesh Haloi, Suhas Roy, Ramananda Bandyopadhyay alongside their contemporary counterparts, Chandra Bhattacharya, Shyam Kanu, Debabrata and Chanchal Mukherjee, to name a few.																								 Event: An exhibition of Indian art and sculpture																								When: Till March 31; 10.30 am -7.30 pm																								Where: Idiyas Gallery; 15 Dover Road
